  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Strengthening the Linkages Between the Formal Justice System and the Traditional Dispute Resolution System to Improve Access to Justice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Traditional Dispute Resolution (TDR) Unit within the Ministry of Justice.
Indirect beneficiaries: Somali citizens, particularly vulnerable groups such as women, marginalized groups and children.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to promote the establishment of a stable and efficient judicial system in Somalia, able to guarantee quality and accessibility of justice services to local systems, which can handle low-risk disengaged combatants and monitor dispute caseloads, in line with the new Constitution and international human rights standards.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To enhance the capacity of the Ministry of Justice and NGOs to engage with traditional dispute resolution mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
